      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Currently the `GemmSm120` does not work and will throw the following error:\r\n\r\n```text\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/harry/quack/benchmarks/benchmark_gemm.py\", line 590, in <module>\r\n    run(\r\n    ~~~^\r\n        args.mnkl,\r\n        ^^^^^^^^^^\r\n    ...<24 lines>...\r\n        args.sm120,\r\n        ^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n    )\r\n    ^\r\n  File \"/home/harry/quack/benchmarks/benchmark_gemm.py\", line 436, in run\r\n    compiled_gemm = cute.compile(\r\n        gemm,\r\n    ...<7 lines>...\r\n        current_stream,\r\n    )\r\n  File \"/home/harry/quack/quack/gemm_sm90.py\", line 527, in __call__\r\n    self.kernel(\r\n    ^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n    ...<19 lines>...\r\n    ).launch(\r\n\r\n  File \"/home/harry/quack/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/nvidia_cutlass_dsl/python_packages/cutlass/cutlass_dsl/cutlass.py\", line 1190, in _check_func_args\r\n    raise DSLRuntimeError(\r\n    ...<2 lines>...\r\n    )\r\ncutlass.base_dsl.common.DSLRuntimeError: DSLRuntimeError: Failed to bind arguments to function `kernel` with signature `(self, tiled_mma: cutlass.cute.atom.TiledMma, tma_atom_a: cutlass.cute.atom.CopyAtom, mA_mkl: cutlass.cute.typing.Tensor, tma_atom_b: cutlass.cute.atom.CopyAtom, mB_nkl: cutlass.cute.typing.Tensor, tma_atom_d: Optional[cutlass.cute.atom.CopyAtom], mD_mnl: Optional[cutlass.cute.typing.Tensor], tma_atom_c: Optional[cutlass.cute.atom.CopyAtom], mC_mnl: Optional[cutlass.cute.typing.Tensor], epilogue_params, varlen_params: quack.varlen_utils.VarlenManager.Params, cluster_layout_mnk: cutlass.cute.typing.Layout, a_smem_layout: cutlass.cute.typing.ComposedLayout, b_smem_layout: cutlass.cute.typing.ComposedLayout, epi_smem_layout: cutlass.cute.typing.ComposedLayout, epi_c_smem_layout: cutlass.cute.typing.ComposedLayout, tile_sched_params, TileSchedulerCls: cutlass.base_dsl.typing.Constexpr[typing.Callable])`\r\n  Caused exception: too many positional arguments\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because its parent class `GemmSm90` calls the `kernel` with the following parameters:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/Dao-AILab/quack/blob/a24e4aa1861ccce0419ba41e3cbe9433e192b5ac/quack/gemm_sm90.py#L526-L547\r\n\r\nBut `GemmSm120` does not accept the last `trace_ptr` argument. This commit adds it as a placeholder to fix the invocation.\r\n\r\nBesides, it fixes the kernel selection in `benchmark_gemm.py`, or `is_sm100` will always be true on any newer devices.\r\n\r\nAfter fixing, the SM120 gemm benchmark can run and shows normal performance:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n~/quack/benchmarks$ python3 benchmark_gemm.py --mnkl 8192,4096,8192,1 --tile_shape_mn 128,128 --sm120\r\nRunning Dense GEMM with:\r\nmnkl: (8192, 4096, 8192, 1)\r\nA dtype: BFloat16, B dtype: BFloat16, D dtype: BFloat16, C_dtype: None, Acc dtype: Float32\r\nMatrix majors - A: k, B: k, D: n\r\nTile Shape: (128, 128), Cluster Shape: (1, 1)\r\nTolerance: 0.03\r\nWarmup iterations: 5\r\nIterations: 30\r\nSkip reference checking: False\r\nCuBLAS Average time: 2.424 ms, TFLOPS: 226.8\r\nCute-DSL Average time: 2.391 ms, TFLOPS: 230.0, GB/s: 112\r\nCuBLAS Average time: 2.428 ms, TFLOPS: 226.4\r\n... (truncated)\r\n```\r\n",
